reviews.text: If you're in Thailand and looking for Sunday worship. This is a great English speaking Anglican Church. Services are Sunday morning 7am and 10:00 am English worship. 1:00 pm. Thai whorship service. They have Sunday school for the kids. Potluck lunches after the service to meet and greet.
Nice playgroup on Wednesdays and Fridays. The pastor is very kind and we enjoyed the Sunday service on Easter.
Really moving experience-great interaction with sooo many cultures.
The Christmas morning service was lively and awesome.  There are washrooms (even for the disabled).
A true reflection of God's people a place of worship with dignity I love this church for all people come and be blessed
Surprised by some of these reviews - you’ll never please everyone. Genuinely the best cookies I’ve ever tasted, bought my first box last week and will definitely be back for more!
We love Bens cookies and they had a fab range of flavours here
Great cookies and coffees really worked well. I lived the peanut butter cookie, a real treat
Quite possibly the tastiest cookie I've ever had! Expensive, but to be expected.

Great for cookies. Moist and freshly baked. Lots of variety. 

The milkshakes are average and I wouldn’t have again. But the cookies are a must 👍🏼👍🏼

The food and atmosphere is fantastic. A great mix between casual and fine dining. Their frites and aioli are a great appetizer and their lunch, supper and drink specials are always on point. The wait staff is super friendly and will gladly answer questions about their dishes. The prices are a little high but they are definitely warranted because of the food quality.

The restaurant itself is so beautiful and cozy. I love their appetizers, especially the frites and aioli. They switch up their menu with season dishes. I always love their duck. The staff is always polite and professional. If you are a person who doesn’t like your food touching, I would let them know when ordering because they do stack their food.
Terrific food, moderate prices for lunch menu. Attentive service. Elevated palate.

Really nice atmosphere. Beautiful holiday decorations and friendly staff. Fast service. We ordered the brucheta and it was very tasty. Each meal is served with a choice of soup or salad. They did a great job on the salad. I went with the pasta for my main course, it was really great tasting, but completely drowned in the sauce. Almost soup like. The menu is fairly short but very reasonable priced.

I celebrated my 21st birthday here and I am  impressed with the service and food quality in this place!
I will remember this place for a long time and sure will come back once again 
*Dona was very nice and help to make that evening even better, she also put a birthday candle in my dessert 😱

Quality restaurant, always get good service and treated well here. Food is always very nice, going from the starters which are prepared well and with a wide range of options. Main courses are nicely well prepared as well. Cocktails choices are good.

We have just left Jamie’s Italian and I am so irritated, I wanted to write this review straight away.

The food was terrible, as I have a Nut Allergy the starter ended being Philadelphia on a chunk of bread with flakes of salmon. Not great. The main was just dolloped on the plate and looked really uncared for preparation wise. This is completely different from the first time we went about a year ago.

Now, the waitress - wow she really shouldn’t be in hospitality. She would come to our table, start talking then leave halfway through her sentence, still talking! A few odd looks were exchanged between my partner and I. The waitress pretty much chucked the plates on our table, same with the final bill then proceeded to try to shout out loud that we had left her just 88p (we actually tipped her low and left her £3 on top of the 88p because she was horrendous at her job). 

Would never return. Would get better at ASK.

My husband and I had a lovely meal at the restaurant on Saturday. It was our first visit and certainly will not be our last. Food was fab, drinks were very refreshing and service was amazing, I would actually go so far to say it was the best service we have come across in a long time. Can not fault it in any way.
I ate here a few times and I love it. Affordable prices and quality meals.

My daughter and I enjoyed a lovely meal here while visiting Bath.  My daughter is 5 and the spaghetti was a huge hit with her.  I choose a seafood stew from the specials and it was delicious.  The restaurant was busy, but the service was still brilliant

Chilled pub, great to watch a sports game or just have a relaxed bite to eat while chatting. They have a nice bar area and smoking area. And you are bound to have a good time there. The staff there are really fun and have such wonderful personalities.

Good day Royal Oak what a plate of good food as always even with  load shedding 
Love and Blessings 
SANDRA Seebregts (Mr Loubser)
A long-standing and pretty convincing approximation of a traditional English pub. Food wasn't bad. Local crowd, many of them ex-pats. Friendly owners.
Cheapish and cheerful for a quick pub lunch. Good food
Very good food. Cosy pub

Still the best Bloody Mary I have ever had.   I stop in every time I’m in Carbondale.  I have had too many good evenings with friends in the cellar to even begin to count.  Many Friday nights started at The Cellar.
Nice low key joint with great drinks!
Neat spot and have a good selection of drinks.
It's a fun old style bar that's down a long flight of stairs. Great drinks! Fun staff!

Possibly my favorite bar in Carbondale. Just a classic basement bar with a hometown feel. There seems to be a bunch of eccentric characters like you would find in an episode of Cheers. Staff were really friendly and helpful. I can't wait to go back there again. Also, pretty easy to find parking and drinks are inexpensive.
